sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM regions_of_interest
WHERE area > 10000;

SELECT parameter
FROM measurements
WHERE measurement_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(horizontal_spatial_resolution_id) AS average_horizontal_resolution
FROM measurements
WHERE description LIKE '%soil moisture%';

external_knowledge:
- 'twilight' metaphorically refers to the period between day and night, associated with `day_night_id = 1`;
- 'keys' metaphorically refer to the measurement parameters;
- 'meanings' refer to the descriptions of the parameters;
- 'cloaks of format' refers to the data format of the measurements;
- 'simplicity of their attire' means arranging by the data format in ascending order.

sql:
SELECT parameter, COUNT(parameter) AS measurement_count
FROM measurements
GROUP BY parameter;

SELECT AVG(hsr.resolution_value) AS average_horizontal_resolution
FROM measurements m
INNER JOIN horizontal_spatial_resolutions hsr ON m.horizontal_spatial_resolution_id = hsr.resolution_id;

SELECT name
FROM regions_of_interest
WHERE area > 1000000;

external_knowledge:
- 'treasures' refers to the parameters being measured;
- 'enchanted realms' are the names of the regions of interest;
- 'kingdoms' are the unique regions where the measurements are taken;
- 'most dazzling treasures' are those with the highest data quality flags, limited to the top 3 per region.

sql:
SELECT name, description
FROM regions_of_interest
WHERE region_id = 0;

SELECT DISTINCT rois.name, cor.coverage_description
FROM regions_of_interest rois
JOIN coverage_of_regions cor ON rois.region_id = cor.region_id;
